Syntax: brandish

Brandishes a magical staff held in your hand, releasing one charge of its
stored spell. The staff must be equipped in a hold slot (left or right hand)
and must have charges remaining.

When brandished, the staff's stored spell is cast, targeting appropriate
characters in the room based on the spell type:
  - Offensive spells target enemies in the room.
  - Defensive spells target allies and the caster.
  - Self-only spells affect only the caster.

The staff loses one charge per use. When all charges are exhausted the staff
becomes empty and can no longer be brandished.

Brandish imposes a 2-pulse wait state regardless of success.

Restrictions:
  - Must be holding a STAFF-type item.
  - Staff must have at least one charge remaining (value[2] > 0).

See also: recite quaff
